social_posts.post_text: I love it when things match unexpectedly. 💅🏼

Marking the first year my pink lemon tree produced fruit✌🏼🐍
Inspired by my love of food packaging, cans of food that don’t exist. 🫠

I often think about plastic packaging and just how many times a day we interact with it. How many seconds/minutes/hours it’s life span is in our possession and how long it lives on afterward. Also, at the same time, how satisfying some of the shapes are. I made these pics together with @graydonpictures and it made me think of the ocean. 🌊
patterns from the last few days 🥹

After 2 years of only leaves, our potted Plumeria flowered again this year. It’s about 5 years old now and maybe 5x the size it was when I bought it, maybe more. I’d like to think it’s finally grown accustomed to wintering at the studio and summering outside at home. Idk, small joys.
A candle that looks like cheese and a bag of candied sunflower seeds.

🍉🍈 Made my 1st fruit only cake for my friend Sasha’s birthday. The inside was layers of cantaloupe, honeydew and watermelon. 

I made quite a few mistakes along the way but it turned out pretty cute even still. Took a few phone snaps of it finished, better pics next time. 😭🥝
